          "title": "MINUTE READ) [https://archive.ph/YWp4O?utm_source=tldrnewsletter]",
          "summary": "Google engineering head Urs Hölzle plans to increase efficiency by rebalancing the ratio of site reliability engineers to developers through automation. Site reliability engineers manage operations, while software engineers work on infrastructure and products. There is currently one site reliability engineer for every 10 software engineers. The new target will have one site reliability engineer for every 20 software engineers. This has sparked speculation of potential layoffs.",
          "url": null,
          "reading_time_minutes": null,
